<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Brite-ChristmasCheer     12-21 0106</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Brite-Christmas Cheer,0108</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Santa Hats Turn Motorists Snarls to Smiles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GULF BREEZE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A highway maintenance crew has found a
way to turn motorists' snarls into smiles, even at work sites where
traffic must slow to a near halt.
   ``I was getting cussed out 10 to 15 times an hour last week,''
said Ernest Nava, a supervisor for the Florida Department of
Transportation.
   But after his crew began wearing red-and-white Santa Claus hats
this week, ``we did not hear a sour word,'' Nava said.
   He said he got the idea from his 14-year-old son, Shawn, who also
wears one of the furry hats.
</TEXT>
