<HEAD>Inaugural Committee Drops $100,000 Donations Minimum Requirement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President-elect George Bush's inaugural
committee says it will now accept donations of less than $100,000.
   Billed as the most open inaugural celebration ever, the
Presidential Inaugural Committee said the minimum contribution had
been instituted because of time and administrative difficulties in
tracking donations.
   Committee spokesman Ed Cassidy said Tuesday the requirement was
dropped because organizers ``never anticipated the number of people
or corporations that would want to participate ... at various
levels. We've been overwhelmed.''
   Cassidy said the change will help ``as many other individuals and
corporations to participate as possible.''
