<HEAD>Metzenbaum Gives Manager Of Winning Campaign $50,000 Bonus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Even before his reelection was official, Sen.
Howard Metzenbaum rewarded his campaign manager with a $50,000
bonus, according to records on file with the Federal Election
Commission.
   The Ohio Democrat last month overwhelmingly defeated Cleveland
Mayor George Voinovich in the most expensive campaign in the state's
history.
   Together, the two candidates spent more than $16 million _ far
exceeding the $3.9 million spent by Sen. John Glenn, D-Ohio and GOP
challenger James Betz, who set the previous state spending record in
1980.
   Among Metzenbaum's disbursements were more than $80,000 in
election-day bonuses, including $50,000 to campaign manger Peter
Harris.
