<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF-PoliteRobber     12-21 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Polite Robber,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Robber Said `Please' As He Held Up Bank</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPOKANE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bank robber who said ``please'' may be
the same one who said ``thank you'' in pulling off an earlier heist,
police say.
   A holdup Monday at a Great Western Savings Bank branch resembled
robberies Nov. 16 at a bank in Shadle Center and Nov. 30 at another
Great Western branch, Lt. John Goldman said.
   In each case, the robber entered shortly before closing time and
did not display a weapon, although he indicated he had one, Goldman
said.
   Police did not disclose the amount of money taken.
   On Monday, a hooded robber told a teller to ``please'' put all of
her money onto the counter, Goldman said. In one of the earlier
holdups, he said, the robber thanked the teller after getting the
cash.
</TEXT>
