<TEXT>
   Nigel Olney, Britain's longest
surviving heart transplant patient, died today almost nine years
after undergoing the life-saving procedure. He was 44.
   Olney underwent a second heart transplant two weeks ago at
Papworth Hospital near Cambridge and had been making a good recovery
until his condition deteriorated Monday, the hospital said.
   Olney, divorced with two teen-age children, had worked as a
fund-raiser for the hospital since his first operation in January
