<HEAD>Gunmen Kill Family of Seven</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen slaughtered a rural family of
seven in the 80th massacre in Colombia this year, the national
police said today.
   Government investigators have said right-wing death squads are
suspected in most of the 640 killings so far this year.
   There was no immediate indication of who killed the family of
seven Tuesday night, the national police said in a news release.
   The reported killings were near the village of Patia, 120 miles
southwest of the capital of Bogota.
