<HEAD>North Dakota Man Sues After Finding Bug In Bag</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FARGO, N.D. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who claims he bit into a beetle while
eating a bag of sunflower seeds has sued the maker of the seeds for
$100,000.
   Tommie Willard of Grand Forks contends Beatrice-Hunt-Wesson Inc.
was negligent in producing the bag of seeds. The complaint seeks
$50,000 each for Willard and his wife, Laura Kay.
   Originally, the complaint was filed in Grand Forks County
District Court, but lawyers for Beatrice this week requested the
lawsuit be transferred to U.S. District Court in Fargo.
   The complaint alleges Willard bit into the beetle Aug. 12 while
eating Fisher Salted in the Shell sunflower seeds. It contends
Willard suffered emotional, mental and physical trauma and
difficulty in sleeping as a result.
   Harlan Fuglesten, a lawyer for Beatrice, said Tuesday the company
denies the allegations in the complaint, but he declined to
elaborate.
