<HEAD>Authorities Demand Foreigners be Allowed on Banned Islands</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities in the republic of
Croatia are demanding the government lift a 15-year-old ban that has
kept foreigners away from two islands in the Adriatic Sea, an
official report said Wednesday.
   Vis and Lastovo, located on a militarily strategic route off the
Croatian coast, were declared off-limits when the navy started
fortifying them in the 1970s, the Tanjug news agency said.
   The ban has irked inhabitants, whose tourism trade suffered.
