<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--FlamingTree     12-21 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Flaming Tree,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Burns to Death Trying to Put Out Blazing Christmas Tree</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman trying to put out her blazing
Christmas tree was enveloped in flames and killed, authorities said
Wednesday.
   ``If you've ever seen a Christmas tree catch fire, you know they
burn very intensely,'' fire Chief Robert Brown said. ``The tree was
found on top of her and a pan of water was found close to her body.''
   Tammie Brown, 26, apparently got the water from her kitchen in an
attempt to extinguish the fire and burned to death, investigators
said.
   It took firefighters five minutes to put out Tuesday's blaze,
which was confined to the living room and kitchen, the fire chief
said. There was no immediate word on what caused the fire.
</TEXT>
