<HEAD>Woman Again Charged With Violating Order To Avoid Michael Jackson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former legal secretary who claims to be
married to Michael Jackson pleaded innocent to violating a court
order to stay away from the pop singer's home.
   Lavon Muhammad, 40, who calls herself Billie Jean Jackson, has
been harassing Jackson for five years by loitering near his home and
misrepresenting herself as his wife, said Deputy City Attorney Davis
Kestenbaum.
   Miss Muhammad was arrested Friday for violating a restraining
order issued last year prohibiting her from loitering outside
Jackson's home in suburban Encino. She pleaded innocent to the
charge Tuesday, the prosecutor said.
   The woman was released on $5,000 bail and faces a Jan. 10 trial.
If convicted, she could be sentenced to up to one year in jail and
fined $1,000.
   Jackson secured the restraining order against Miss Muhammad, who
has been convicted three times of trespassing on Jackson's property.
   She was carrying a bottle of champagne when arrested in February
after scaling a backyard fence at 3 a.m. Miss Muhammad's most recent
arrest came Dec. 7 as she stood near Jackson's home, court records
show.
   The woman claims she was the inspiration for the singer's hit
song ``Billie Jean,'' about a woman of that name who claims she bore
Jackson's child. Miss Muhammad says Jackson, 30, fathered her
6-year-old twins.
