<HEAD>Iraq Promises Adherence To OPEC Quotas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iraq has pledged to srictly abide by OPEC's
recent production agreement and is asking other members to do the
same, OPEC President Rilwanu Lukman says.
   The government-owned Lagos Times reported Wednesday that Lukman
had received a letter from Iraqi Oil Minister Issam Al Chalabi
promising strict adherence to the production agreement reached last
month by the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries.
   The cartel agreed to cut daily production to 18.5 million barrels
to help drive up sagging worldwide oil prices.
   In the letter to Lukman, the Iraqi minister said compliance was
necessary ``so that the objectives of our organization are fulfilled
and the interest of all member countries served.''
   The minister also said that Kuwait and Saudi Arabia would stop
sending war relief crude oil to Iraq from Jan. 1.
