<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Close Lower In Light Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks finished lower on the London stock exchange
Wednesday, reflecting a lack of fresh news and the approaching long
holiday weekend.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 4.8
points, or 0.3 percent, to 1,772.6, near the session low of 1,771.8.
The index's best level of the day was 1,776.9.
   By the end of trading, the narrower Financial Times 30-share
index was off 3.3 points at 1,435.0.
   Volume totaled 465 million shares, compared with the 454.5
million shares Tuesday.
   The Financial Times 500-share index fell 2.1 points to close at
995.02.
</TEXT>
