<2ND_LINE>BC-Saturn Card,0108</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Like The Car, Saturn Christmas Card a Secret</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of the tighest-held secrets around General
Motors Corp. is just what its new Saturn Corp. car will look like
when it's introduced in late 1990.
   The secrecy has carried over to this year's holiday card from the
GM subsidiary.
   ``After months of exhaustive effort,'' reads the card's cover,
``the Saturn Corporation has developed a beautiful and economical
holiday greeting card.''
   And inside:
   ``But we've decided not to show it until sometime in 1990.''
   Saturn spokesman Mark Tanner said the card's text was a team
effort.
</TEXT>
